pygments API Documentation Modules Classes Names

Search bar offers the following options:

  • Term presence. The below example searches for documents that must contain “foo”, might contain “bar” and must not contain “baz”: +foo bar -baz
  • Wildcards. The below example searches for documents with words beginning with “foo”: foo*
  • Search in specific fields. The following search matches all objects in "twisted.mail" that matches “search”: +qname:twisted.mail.* +search

    Possible fields: 'name', 'qname' (fully qualified name), 'docstring', and 'kind'. Last two fields are only applicable if "search in docstrings" is enabled.

  • Fuzzy matches. The following search matches all documents that have a word within 1 edit distance of “foo”: foo~1

  • pygments.lexer.Lexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexer.Lexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.actionscript.ActionScript3Lexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.actionscript.ActionScript3Lexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC

    pygments.lexers.perl.PerlLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    pygments.lexers.algebra.GAPLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.asc.AscLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.asc.AscLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.bdd.BddLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.bdd.BddLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.c_like.SwigLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.c_like.SwigLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.prolog.PrologLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.prolog.PrologLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.graphics.PovrayLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.graphics.PovrayLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    POVRAY is similar to JSON/C, but the combination of camera and light_source is probably not very likely elsewhere. HLSL or GLSL are similar (GLSL even has #version), but they miss #declare, and light_source/camera are not keywords anywhere else -- it's fair to assume though that any POVRAY scene must have a camera and lightsource.

  • pygments.lexers.shell.BashLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.shell.BashLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.shell.ExeclineLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.shell.ExeclineLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.configs.IniLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.configs.IniLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.javascript.LassoLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.javascript.LassoLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.dalvik.SmaliLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.dalvik.SmaliLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.theorem.CoqLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.theorem.CoqLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.gdscript.GDScriptLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.gdscript.GDScriptLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.inferno.LimboLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.inferno.LimboLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.modeling.BugsLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.modeling.BugsLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    pygments.lexers.sql.SqlLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.testing.GherkinLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.testing.GherkinLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC

  • pygments.lexers.resource.ResourceLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.resource.ResourceLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.templates.SqlJinjaLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.templates.SqlJinjaLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.

  • pygments.lexers.varnish.VCLLexer.analyse_text
    pygments.lexers.varnish.VCLLexer.html#analyse_text
    Function
    Method
    PUBLIC
    Has to return a float between ``0`` and ``1`` that indicates if a lexer wants to highlight this text. Used by ``guess_lexer``. If this method returns ``0`` it won't highlight it in any case, if it returns ``1`` highlighting with this lexer is guaranteed.
